    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan before we proceed:\n\n## Plan: `uv cache stats`\n\n**4 files touched, 1 new file created.**\n\n### What I found in the codebase\n\n- **`CacheBucket::iter()`** yields 10 variants (`Wheels`, `SourceDistributions`, `FlatIndex`, `Git`, `Interpreter`, `Simple`, `Archive`, `Builds`, `Environments`, `Binaries`) — excludes `Python`, which is intentional.\n- **`Display` for `CacheBucket`** delegates to `to_str()`, producing versioned names like `\"wheels-v6\"`, `\"sdists-v9\"`, etc. — exactly what we want to print.\n- **`diskus::DiskUsage::count_ignoring_errors()`** silently returns `0` for non-existent paths, so we don't need explicit existence checks per bucket.\n- **`cache_size.rs`** has a preview feature guard — `cache_stats.rs` does **not** need one (the new command is not gated behind a preview flag per the spec).\n- No new crate dependencies are needed — `diskus`, `human_readable_bytes`, and all other imports are already available in `crates/uv`.\n\n### Changes at a glance\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs` | Add `Stats(StatsArgs)` variant + new `StatsArgs` struct (mirrors `SizeArgs`) |\n| `crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs` | **New file**: iterate buckets, print `\"{bucket}: {size}\"` per line, then `\"total: {size}\"` |\n| `crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs` | `mod cache_stats;` + `pub(crate) use cache_stats::cache_stats;` |\n| `crates/uv/src/lib.rs` | Dispatch arm `CacheCommand::Stats(args) => commands::cache_stats(...)` after `Size` arm |",
